# @dome/backend environment

Copy to `.env` for local overrides.

```bash
# HTTP server
DOME_BACKEND_HOST=127.0.0.1
DOME_BACKEND_PORT=8788

# Chain / contracts (defaults read from .dome-local/base-deploy.json)
DOME_DEPLOY_FILE=.dome-local/base-deploy.json
DOME_BASE_RPC_UPSTREAM=http://127.0.0.1:8545
DOME_ETH_POOL_ADDRESS=
DOME_CHAIN_ID=31337

# Relayer (Hardhat account #0 is allowed only on chain 31337)
DOME_RELAYER_PRIVATE_KEY=0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80

# Local dev faucet (disabled automatically on testnet via deploy script)
DOME_DEV_FAUCET=true

# Indexer persistence (SQLite local, Postgres testnet)
DOME_SQLITE_PATH=.dome-local/backend.sqlite
# DOME_DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@host:5432/dome

# Security / limits
DOME_RELAYER_SECRET=
DOME_RATE_LIMIT_RPC_PER_MIN=240
DOME_RATE_LIMIT_RELAYER_PER_MIN=20
```

See `.env.sepolia.example` for Base Sepolia.
